<img src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-864472 lazyload" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-974x548.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/mg5193-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />MTN Group’s newly acquired music streaming entity, Simfy Africa, has been given a welcome boost with the appointment of Oyebowale Akideinde as Head of Over The Top (OTT) Music Services. The appointment, which has since taken effective from February 1, will enhance the company’s digital music streaming services to its customers across Africa and the Middle East. Oyebowale joins MTN from Boomplay Music where he served as the Regional Director for West Africa. His career spans over 17 years primarily in consumer goods, e-business, financial, media and digital sectors. He has also worked in IT, project management, strategy, product and business development, and marketing. He holds an MSc in Business Information Systems from the University of Hertfordshire, a BSc in Computer Science from the University of Lagos and a General Music Studies Specialist Certificate from Berklee College of Music. Oyebowale has also garnered a number of industry related awards and accolades throughout his career. Commenting on the appointment, MTN Group President and CEO, Rob Shuter said, “We are very pleased about Oye’s appointment as he brings passion and knowledge of the rich media industry. This will stand him in good stead to support MTN’s expansion of OTT digital services to our customers.”